sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M11207
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Device containing HXT7/mNarK promoters and GFP/RFP to monitor glucose/oxygen levels in S. cerevisiae
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Composite of the following BioBrick devices: BBa_M11204, BBa_M11206
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Used in S. cerevisiae to monitor glucose and oxygen levels. It is composed of two BioBrick devices:
Device 1: The promoter, HXT7, is repressed in the presence of glucose. The promoter is followed by the Kozak sequence Ribosome Binding Site. After the RBS, is the GFP sequence codon optimized for S. cerevisiae. It is ended with the ADH1 terminator for S. cerevisiae.
Device 2: The promoter, mNarK , is activated under anaerobic condtions. The promoter is followed by the Kozak sequence Ribosome Binding Site. After the RBS, is the RFP sequence codon optimized for S. cerevisiae. It is ended with the ADH1 terminator for S. cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Angela Dixon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K239006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Raw genomic sequence from biocyc, Escherichia coli K-12, but modified.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence contains 2 Fnr (one of which is modified), 1 Fis, 2 NarL binding sites and initiates transcription by RNAP sigma-70. Function: Switched on during anaerobic conditions. Area of application: Detection of when the cell is switching to anaerobic metabolism.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Detect and remove possible restriction sites: XbaI, EcoRI, PstI, SpeI, AgeI, BamHI, BglII, NogMIV, NotI and XhoI. No restriction site had to be removed. Sequence starts 3 bp before the first FNR binding site and ends 6 pb after the -10 box. One pb has been changed in order optimise the first FNR binding site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Axel Nystrom
